SECTION 7: DEBUGGING GUIDE FOR COMMON ISSUES
================================================================================

ISSUE: Agent loops repeatedly, calls same tool multiple times
FIX:
  1. Add max_iterations limit (set it, don't rely on default)
  2. Add action history tracking — if same action+input seen 3 times, break
  3. Improve tool descriptions to include "Do NOT repeat this query"
  4. Add state tracking so agent knows what it has already done

ISSUE: Tool calls fail frequently
FIX:
  1. Add Pydantic input validation (catch bad inputs before execution)
  2. Add retry logic with exponential backoff
  3. Add debug logging to see exact inputs/outputs
  4. Test tool independently outside of agent

ISSUE: Slow response times
FIX:
  1. Route simple queries to 8B model (not 70B)
  2. Parallelize independent tool calls (ThreadPoolExecutor)
  3. Implement caching for repeated queries (hash-based cache)
  4. Set max_tokens limits appropriate to task
  5. Deploy via NVIDIA NIM (automatic optimization)
  6. Enable streaming (improve perceived latency)

ISSUE: Inconsistent/unpredictable responses
FIX:
  1. Lower temperature (0.1-0.3 for classification/routing decisions)
  2. Use structured outputs (Pydantic output parser with schema)
  3. Add response validation with retry
  4. Use few-shot examples in prompt to anchor behavior

ISSUE: Context window overflow
FIX:
  1. Implement ConversationBufferWindowMemory with appropriate k
  2. Use ConversationSummaryMemory for long sessions
  3. Monitor token count, trigger truncation proactively
  4. Reduce chunk sizes in RAG pipeline

ISSUE: Agent uses wrong tool
FIX:
  1. Rewrite tool descriptions to be more specific
  2. Add "when to use" and "when NOT to use" to descriptions
  3. Use Pydantic schema so tool clearly shows what input it expects
  4. Reduce number of tools (fewer choices = easier selection)


================================================================================
SECTION 8: ANTI-PATTERNS (WHAT NOT TO DO)
================================================================================

SILENT EXCEPTION EATING:
  BAD: except: pass
  GOOD: except Exception as e: logger.error(...); return fallback()

UNBOUNDED LOOPS:
  BAD: while not done: act()
  GOOD: for i in range(max_iterations): if done: break; act()

HARDCODED PROMPTS:
  BAD: llm.invoke("You are a bot. Answer: " + query)
  GOOD: PromptTemplate(input_variables=["query"], template="...")

NO INPUT VALIDATION:
  BAD: def tool(user_input): return api_call(user_input)
  GOOD: Validate length, sanitize, check format before calling API

EXPOSING INTERNAL ERRORS:
  BAD: return f"Error: {str(e)}"  # Exposes stack trace to user
  GOOD: logger.error(str(e)); return "Service temporarily unavailable"

HARDCODED API KEYS:
  BAD: api_key = "nvapi-abc123..."
  GOOD: api_key = os.getenv("NVIDIA_API_KEY")

SEQUENTIAL INDEPENDENT CALLS:
  BAD: r1 = tool1(a); r2 = tool2(b); r3 = tool3(c)  # 3 seconds total
  GOOD: ThreadPoolExecutor concurrent execution → 1 second total

IGNORING RATE LIMITS:
  BAD: [agent.invoke(q) for q in 10000_queries]  # Hammers API
  GOOD: RateLimitedAgent wrapper with requests-per-minute tracking


