SECTION 9: HIGH-PROBABILITY EXAM SCENARIOS WITH REASONING
================================================================================

SCENARIO 1:
Q: API fails 10% of time with 503. Recovers in 5 seconds. Users expect <10s.
A: Retry with exponential backoff: 3 attempts at 1s, 2s, 4s delays.
   Total max wait: 7s, well under 10s budget.
   Only retry 5xx (503 = server error, transient).

SCENARIO 2:
Q: Agent using 70B model takes 5s/response. 80% are simple FAQs.
   How to reduce latency while maintaining quality for complex queries?
A: Hybrid routing — classify query complexity (with fast 8B model), route
   simple queries to 8B (<1s), complex to 70B (5s). Average latency drops
   dramatically since 80% hit fast path. Both deployed via NIM.

SCENARIO 3:
Q: Need to call 5 independent APIs, each takes 1s. Need <2s total response.
A: Parallelize with ThreadPoolExecutor. All 5 calls execute concurrently
   → ~1s total + overhead. Sequential = 5s, concurrent = ~1s.

SCENARIO 4:
Q: Service is down for 30+ minutes. Agent keeps timing out on every request.
A: Circuit Breaker. After 5 consecutive failures, open the circuit.
   Requests immediately return error/fallback without calling the service.
   After 60s, half-open: test one request. If succeeds, close circuit.

SCENARIO 5:
Q: Agent needs to categorize feedback as positive/negative/neutral then
   generate appropriate response. Most effective prompting strategy?
A: Chain-of-Thought + few-shot examples.
   CoT: Think through the sentiment first, then generate response.
   Few-shot: Provide 2-3 examples per sentiment class to anchor behavior.
   Temperature: 0.2-0.3 for classification reliability.

SCENARIO 6:
Q: Users report agent gives inconsistent answers to same question.
A: Multiple fixes: Lower temperature (0.1), add structured output parser
   (forces consistent format), add few-shot examples,
   add response validation layer with retry.

SCENARIO 7:
Q: You want to A/B test a new prompt template. How?
A: Route 50% traffic to old (Variant A) and 50% to new (Variant B).
   Collect user satisfaction ratings for each.
   After 100+ samples per variant, compare average ratings.
   Use statistical significance testing. Winner becomes new production prompt.

SCENARIO 8:
Q: Production agent sometimes returns partial/truncated responses.
A: Set appropriate max_tokens (e.g., 1024 for detailed tasks).
   Add response validation: check minimum length, retry if truncated.
   If streaming: check on_llm_end fires without truncation error.


